&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DEPARTMENT OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GILLIG Engineering is responsible for the development, customization, and configuration of GILLIG’s clean technology heavy-duty transit buses.&amp;nbsp; We are committed to developing the most reliable buses that connect communities, eliminates congestion, and contributes to a greener environment.&amp;nbsp; Our engineers are engaged in designing, analyzing, testing, launching, and problem solving across a wide range of technical areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liaison Engineering serves as the critical link between design and manufacturing teams, ensuring smooth and efficient production of GILLIG’s high-quality transit buses. Their core mission is to bridge the gap between engineering design and the manufacturing floor in Livermore, CA. They support current products, facilitate seamless integration of new designs and ensure continuous improvement of production processes. The Liaison Engineering Group is a cross-functional and multi-talented group, housing mechanical, electrical, vehicle controls, and industrial engineering as well as dedicated production support technicians to ensure coverage in all facets of producing transit buses.&lt;/p&gt;
