&lt;h4&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GILLIG is seeking an experienced Manager, Payroll to lead and oversee all payroll operations across the organization. This role is responsible for ensuring accurate, timely, and compliant payroll processing while driving operational excellence, process improvements, and payroll system optimization.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Manager, Payroll serves as the subject matter expert for payroll compliance, taxation, payroll systems, and reporting. This position partners closely with Human Resources, Finance, HRIS, and external vendors to maintain payroll integrity, support organizational growth, and ensure employees are paid accurately and on time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The ideal candidate possesses deep expertise in SAP SuccessFactors Employee Central Payroll, UKG Time &amp;amp; Attendance (Kronos), payroll compliance, and payroll operations management, along with demonstrated experience leading payroll teams and cross-functional initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
